-- Israel Stocks: Ampal-American, Delek Group, Avner, Negev, Migdal
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-01-15T15:15:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/israel-stocks-ampal-american-delek-group-avner-negev-migdal.html
Israel ’s  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  closed at its
lowest level since Jan. 1, retreating 1.9 percent to 1,107.26,
at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. The measure has gained 2
percent this year after dropping 18 percent in 2011.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ampal-American Israel (AMPL)  Corp, the owner of a 12.5
percent stake in a company that exports gas from  Egypt  to
Israel, gained 4.6 percent, the biggest jump since Jan. 10, to
1.546 shekels, or the equivalent of $0.40. Ampal’s U.S.-traded
stock surged 15 percent in  New York  to $0.4276 on Jan. 13.  Delek Group Ltd. (DLEKG)   dropped the most since Dec. 12,
declining 4.9 percent, to 760 shekels. Delek’s oil and gas
exploring unit, Delek Drilling-LP (DEDRL IT), issued a reserves
update which showed lower estimates for oil quantities at the
Leviathan site. Delek Drilling lost 4.7 percent to 14.85
shekels.  Avner Oil Exploration LLP (AVNRL)   slumped 5 percent
to 2.58 shekels.  Ratio Oil Exploration 1992 LP  (RATIL IT), a
partner in the Leviathan site, dropped 12 percent to 0.365
shekel.  Negev Ceramics Ltd. (NGEV)   jumped 8 percent to 23.49
shekels, the highest close since at least February 1996, when
Bloomberg began tracking the stock.  Africa Israel Industries
Ltd. (AFID)   offered to buy the remaining 10 percent of the
tile maker for 23 shekels a share.  Migdal Insurance & Financial Holding Ltd.  (MGDL IT) surged
the most since August 2009, climbing 5.9 percent o 5.70 shekels.
The insurance company said controlling shareholder Assicurazioni
Generali SpA received bids for a holding in the Israeli company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
